  "body": "Quoting Francesca:\r\n\r\nas confirmed by Pedro and John on discord and [here](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/16235#issuecomment-1612919707) we have 3 possible behaviors:\r\n\r\n- if at the bottom: the composer pushes content up.\r\n- if on scroll: the composer still pushes content up until a certain threshold (half the screen maybe, as suggested by Omar) to allow users to reply to a message and still see the message they're replying to, as much as possible. This will eventually be impossible if the message we're typing becomes too long, in that case (after the threshold) the composer will cover the whole screen. \r\n- If the user manually stretches by dragging the handle it shouldn't push content up.",
